WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:12.105 --> 00:14.105
[birds cawing faintly]

00:15.688 --> 00:17.688
[menacing music building]

00:26.480 --> 00:28.688
[menacing music intensifying]

00:58.480 --> 00:59.896
[music trails off]

01:05.021 --> 01:07.271
[energy thrumming]

01:07.355 --> 01:08.188
[grunts]

01:08.855 --> 01:09.688
Ooh.

01:10.188 --> 01:12.146
[shadowy figure] Well, this is awkward.

01:14.646 --> 01:18.771
I didn't realize the heist
had such a specific dress code.

01:20.063 --> 01:23.980
And here I came in my Easter best.

01:26.646 --> 01:28.771
What the fuck is that thing?

01:28.855 --> 01:30.563
It's a rabbit?

01:30.646 --> 01:32.396
I don't care what it is. Kill it.

01:32.480 --> 01:33.688
Oh.

01:33.771 --> 01:35.396
There's no need for that.

01:36.021 --> 01:40.230
Americans,
the most dependable of your species.

01:40.313 --> 01:43.563
Anything that doesn't fit
your narrow understanding,

01:43.646 --> 01:47.396
you shoot, bomb,
or burn without hesitation.

01:47.480 --> 01:48.438
[chuckles wryly]

01:49.146 --> 01:51.188
And look where it's gotten you.

01:51.271 --> 01:53.980
Four so-called soldiers of fortune

01:54.063 --> 01:59.396
stealing common stones
for a mere 2.5 million,

02:00.188 --> 02:03.021
when there's something
right in front of you

02:03.105 --> 02:05.396
that is beyond earthly value.

02:05.480 --> 02:08.855
Wait. How do you know
the price we were offered?

02:08.938 --> 02:11.063
I was the one who offered it.

02:11.146 --> 02:12.146
[glass cracking]

02:14.855 --> 02:16.271
[energy thrums]

02:17.146 --> 02:18.271
[klaxon wails]

02:20.938 --> 02:22.855
The Force Edge.

02:22.938 --> 02:25.730
Sword of the demon knight Sparda.

02:26.313 --> 02:27.396
Ironic, isn't it,

02:27.480 --> 02:32.438
that such a holy place would house
the most powerful weapon of Hell?

02:32.521 --> 02:36.938
Then again, Hell, as you call it,

02:37.021 --> 02:40.813
has always been
the true heart of human religion.

02:40.896 --> 02:43.146
You can curb the worst of your savageries

02:43.230 --> 02:47.646
only through collective fear
and hatred of another world.

02:48.230 --> 02:50.105
My world.

02:51.146 --> 02:52.855
You talk a lot for a rabbit.

02:53.355 --> 02:57.396
Take what you want, long as you
still pay Rampart for this operation.

02:57.896 --> 03:02.771
Rest assured,
you will be paid everything you're owed.

03:03.938 --> 03:04.855
[gagging]

03:07.730 --> 03:09.730
[dark, brooding music playing]

03:09.813 --> 03:10.771
[agents gasping]

03:15.646 --> 03:17.563
[bullets ricocheting]

03:25.313 --> 03:26.313
[rabbit giggling]

03:31.480 --> 03:32.480
[gasps]

03:33.063 --> 03:38.605
Here we stand together
on the threshold of a new age,

03:38.688 --> 03:41.105
the age of the Demon.

03:41.188 --> 03:47.271
This world is about to become
much, much larger.

03:47.355 --> 03:49.646
Well, not for you.

04:01.646 --> 04:03.688
[sinister choral music playing]

04:16.313 --> 04:17.313
[music halts]

04:19.188 --> 04:21.188
[ambient street noise]

04:33.563 --> 04:34.563
[cooing]

04:35.646 --> 04:36.563
Sorry.

04:36.646 --> 04:37.480
So-- [grunts]

04:38.271 --> 04:40.230
Hey, excuse me.

04:40.313 --> 04:41.938
Excuse yourself, lady.

04:44.896 --> 04:45.730
Asshole!

04:50.688 --> 04:52.146
[shrill stinger plays]

05:04.396 --> 05:06.688
Goddamn it, Ellie. What now?

05:09.563 --> 05:11.563
[uneasy rustling, clattering]

05:14.896 --> 05:18.563
[sighs] You always pick
the worst possible time, don't you?

05:18.646 --> 05:22.146
If I didn't know better,
I'd swear you did this on purpose.

05:25.230 --> 05:26.813
[distressing music playing]

05:26.896 --> 05:28.313
[throaty gurgling]

05:30.605 --> 05:31.605
[woman screams]

05:33.730 --> 05:35.730
-[woman straining]
-[shadow gurgling]

05:44.063 --> 05:46.271
[choking] Please, take me.

05:46.771 --> 05:49.771
Don't hurt my daughter.

05:50.355 --> 05:53.396
What daughter?

05:55.605 --> 05:58.396
Hey, look!
The Three Stooges came out to play.

05:59.563 --> 06:01.063
[rowdy rock music playing]

06:23.188 --> 06:24.021
Jackpot!

06:30.938 --> 06:31.980
[woman coughing]

06:35.896 --> 06:37.396
[heavy metal music building]

06:39.813 --> 06:41.021
[song halts abruptly]

06:41.105 --> 06:45.646
Eh, the way this usually goes is,
I do that then drop a killer one-liner.

06:45.730 --> 06:47.646
But I'm drawing a complete blank now.

06:47.730 --> 06:49.480
This never happens to me, I swear.

06:49.980 --> 06:50.813
Okay, wait.

06:50.896 --> 06:53.063
I got one. Pretend I just shot that guy.

06:53.563 --> 06:54.563
Bang!

06:55.396 --> 06:59.063
Man, Skeletor did not hold up
since the '80s.

07:00.230 --> 07:01.563
Not my best work, but you get it.

07:02.313 --> 07:03.313
[sighs wearily]

07:05.146 --> 07:08.646
Um, I don't know how to thank you.

07:08.730 --> 07:10.063
You saved our lives.

07:10.813 --> 07:13.563
That is why you're here, right?
To save us?

07:14.146 --> 07:14.980
More or less.

07:15.480 --> 07:18.980
There have been other attacks in the area.
My client hired me to look into it.

07:19.063 --> 07:21.021
Your client?

07:21.105 --> 07:23.938
What kind of work do you do, exactly?

07:24.438 --> 07:25.480
Demon hunting.

07:25.563 --> 07:29.563
[woman] Wait, you're telling me
they were actually…

07:29.646 --> 07:30.688
What, those guys?

07:30.771 --> 07:32.396
Those are just low-level demons.

07:32.480 --> 07:33.730
Nothing to worry about.

07:33.813 --> 07:35.271
[ominous music droning]

07:35.355 --> 07:36.355
[music halts abruptly]

07:41.563 --> 07:42.396
Cute kid.

07:42.480 --> 07:43.688
[sputters]

07:44.188 --> 07:46.563
We really should be getting home now.

07:46.646 --> 07:47.980
Shouldn't we, Ellie?

07:48.063 --> 07:49.771
Say goodbye to the nice man.

07:49.855 --> 07:51.063
[giggling]

07:51.146 --> 07:52.146
[demonic shrieking]

07:54.855 --> 07:56.688
[rowdy rock music building]

07:57.480 --> 07:59.730
[shrill yowling]

08:03.688 --> 08:06.230
Stop! What are you doing? That's my baby!

08:06.313 --> 08:07.521
No, it's not--

08:07.605 --> 08:08.605
[music halts]

08:09.271 --> 08:10.271
[grunts]

08:18.480 --> 08:19.480
Damn it.

08:27.021 --> 08:29.313
["Rollin’ (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

08:29.396 --> 08:31.188
♪ Throw your hands up ♪

08:31.271 --> 08:33.730
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

08:33.813 --> 08:36.480
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

08:36.563 --> 08:39.230
♪ I move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

08:39.313 --> 08:41.646
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

08:41.730 --> 08:44.355
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

08:44.438 --> 08:46.521
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

08:46.605 --> 08:49.313
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

08:49.396 --> 08:51.730
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

08:51.813 --> 08:54.146
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

08:54.230 --> 08:56.730
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

08:56.813 --> 08:58.938
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

08:59.021 --> 09:01.813
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

09:01.896 --> 09:03.980
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

09:04.063 --> 09:06.813
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

09:06.896 --> 09:08.896
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

09:08.980 --> 09:11.480
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

09:11.563 --> 09:14.438
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

09:14.521 --> 09:16.646
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

09:16.730 --> 09:19.396
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

09:19.480 --> 09:21.896
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

09:21.980 --> 09:24.105
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

09:24.188 --> 09:26.938
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

09:27.021 --> 09:29.021
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

09:29.105 --> 09:31.771
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

09:31.855 --> 09:34.480
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

09:34.563 --> 09:35.563
[song trails off]

09:42.605 --> 09:45.521
[synth jingle plays]

09:45.605 --> 09:47.605
[muffled explosions, screaming]

09:49.313 --> 09:53.230
This is the first image released
from last night's Vatican City bombings

09:53.313 --> 09:56.105
that have shocked and horrified
the entire world.

09:56.188 --> 10:00.313
The suspect appears to have
two strange protrusions on his back

10:00.396 --> 10:03.730
that are shaped almost like wings.

10:04.230 --> 10:06.105
[reporter 1] A world in mourning.

10:06.188 --> 10:08.855
One question weighs on the minds of all.

10:08.938 --> 10:11.605
Who could be responsible?

10:11.688 --> 10:14.563
The radical left is already using this
to push their agenda

10:14.646 --> 10:16.813
that America should step down
from our role as,

10:16.896 --> 10:19.521
quote-unquote, "global policemen."

10:19.605 --> 10:23.771
But as the greatest country on Earth,
we have a moral responsibility to lead.

10:23.855 --> 10:25.146
Not to mention,

10:25.230 --> 10:28.855
the surveillance image clearly shows
some sort of weaponized wing-suit.

10:28.938 --> 10:31.771
That is not any US military technology
that I know of.

10:31.855 --> 10:36.396
Exactly. With tech like that,
it was probably the Russians.

10:36.480 --> 10:38.521
[commentator] Now, the government,

10:38.605 --> 10:39.938
the corporatists that own it,

10:40.021 --> 10:42.855
and their loyal propagandists
in the news media

10:42.938 --> 10:44.896
want you to blame the Russians.

10:44.980 --> 10:48.771
[scoffs] How stupid
do they think we are, folks? Hmm?

10:49.355 --> 10:51.730
This was a strike against God himself!

10:51.813 --> 10:55.521
Carried out by a sophisticated network
of terrorist demons.

10:55.605 --> 10:57.271
From Hell!

10:57.355 --> 10:59.355
[studio audience laughing]

10:59.438 --> 11:01.313
Uh, terrorist demons.

11:01.396 --> 11:04.105
[chuckles] I don't… You hear about this?

11:04.188 --> 11:06.480
I think I missed
that one in Sunday school.

11:06.563 --> 11:09.188
-[audience laughs]
-Ever heard of a terrorist demon, Phil?

11:09.271 --> 11:10.771
Sure. My ex-wife.

11:10.855 --> 11:11.896
[audience laughs]

11:11.980 --> 11:12.980
[rimshot]

11:15.396 --> 11:16.730
[man] The attacks were perpetrated

11:16.813 --> 11:20.646
by what appears to be a sophisticated
network of terrorist demons.

11:20.730 --> 11:22.105
This can't be serious.

11:22.188 --> 11:25.896
Bad enough our Rampart boys were there.
Now we're gonna really entertain--

11:25.980 --> 11:30.896
Dr. Fisher is one of the foremost
theoretical physicists in the world.

11:30.980 --> 11:32.938
I assure you, he is serious.

11:33.021 --> 11:35.438
My apologies, Mr. Vice President.

11:35.521 --> 11:37.938
Let me wrap this around my brain.

11:38.021 --> 11:40.480
How can you be sure
that these things were…

11:40.563 --> 11:41.605
Demons?

11:42.480 --> 11:45.938
The same way that any criminal
is identified, Mr. President.

11:46.021 --> 11:48.146
My team tested DNA samples from the scene.

11:48.230 --> 11:50.605
And you know what demon DNA looks like?

11:51.188 --> 11:53.938
Demons,
since we're using the colloquial term,

11:54.021 --> 11:58.396
are a related but separate
evolutionary branch from Homo sapiens.

11:58.480 --> 12:00.271
They are natives of another universe,

12:00.355 --> 12:02.771
one that exists parallel to our own.

12:02.855 --> 12:06.771
My current hypothesis is that
one of our common ancestors

12:06.855 --> 12:09.521
found their way into this other universe,

12:09.605 --> 12:11.896
where they adapted and became stronger,

12:11.980 --> 12:14.271
able to survive
the more hostile environment.

12:14.355 --> 12:15.355
You mean Hell.

12:15.438 --> 12:20.063
Just to be clear, the hostile environment
you're talking about is Hell.

12:20.146 --> 12:21.896
[chuckles]

12:21.980 --> 12:24.688
Mythology exists to explain reality.

12:25.188 --> 12:27.271
Why do you think every culture on Earth

12:27.355 --> 12:30.855
tells the same stories
about demons and the underworld?

12:31.855 --> 12:34.313
We've discovered an interdimensional rift

12:34.396 --> 12:37.438
that acts as a bridge
between the two universes.

12:37.521 --> 12:42.146
However, it has been blocked for millennia
by a field of quantum interference.

12:42.230 --> 12:44.563
Naturally occurring
disruptions in this field

12:44.646 --> 12:48.480
sometimes create
what one might term portals,

12:48.563 --> 12:51.688
which allow lesser demon types
to enter into our world.

12:51.771 --> 12:54.271
Luckily, these portals
aren't stable enough

12:54.355 --> 12:57.688
to accommodate larger,
more complex molecular structures.

12:57.771 --> 12:59.896
Uh-huh, right.

12:59.980 --> 13:00.980
Which means?

13:01.063 --> 13:04.271
Which means the big demons
are stuck on the other side.

13:04.355 --> 13:06.605
Who do you work for exactly, Doctor?

13:08.938 --> 13:10.771
Dark Realm Command.

13:10.855 --> 13:13.771
DARKCOM, as our PR department
insists we call it.

13:13.855 --> 13:16.688
DARKCOM is an independent
dimensional security firm,

13:16.771 --> 13:19.938
funded by private investments,
such as my own.

13:22.980 --> 13:25.105
Sir! You have to see this!

13:28.271 --> 13:30.813
[rabbit] Sword of the demon knight Sparda.

13:30.896 --> 13:32.021
Sparda?

13:32.105 --> 13:33.730
Now that's interesting.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.730
It looks like that sword is all he took.

13:44.396 --> 13:45.646
[soldier struggling]

13:48.813 --> 13:51.980
The gates of Hell
will be open soon enough.

13:52.813 --> 13:56.396
To any sapiens wishing
to join the celebration,

13:56.896 --> 14:00.855
if you want to catch a rabbit,
find the hunter.

14:01.771 --> 14:03.313
Hope to see you all there.

14:03.813 --> 14:05.855
[soldier screaming]

14:07.771 --> 14:09.688
[haltingly] My God.

14:10.563 --> 14:14.355
All the last guy had to worry about
was Saddam Hussein.

14:14.438 --> 14:18.730
I've already got bio-organic weapons
I've got to deal with.

14:18.813 --> 14:22.313
And now you're telling me
there's demons crawling up out of Hell?

14:22.396 --> 14:25.813
You heard the doctor.
This is no longer a matter of religion.

14:25.896 --> 14:27.230
It's science.

14:27.313 --> 14:30.646
The word of the Lord has been
proven beyond dispute.

14:30.730 --> 14:32.271
Hell is real.

14:32.771 --> 14:35.271
And the Holy War is here.

14:35.355 --> 14:38.521
[Dr. Fisher] "If you want
to catch a rabbit, find the hunter."

14:38.605 --> 14:40.688
I believe the demon is toying with us.

14:40.771 --> 14:42.688
Giving us a clue to its next move.

14:42.771 --> 14:46.771
We need to figure out who this hunter is,
which can only mean…

14:46.855 --> 14:47.855
A demon hunter.

14:48.938 --> 14:51.146
Find every demon hunter you can.

14:51.230 --> 14:52.646
And bring them to me.

14:57.563 --> 14:58.938
What he said.

15:23.896 --> 15:25.896
[mellow music playing]

15:26.771 --> 15:27.813
Right on time.

15:27.896 --> 15:29.730
Your usual's waiting on the bar.

15:29.813 --> 15:31.688
Thanks. I need it today.

15:48.396 --> 15:49.855
[distorted whooshing]

15:49.938 --> 15:51.688
[music warps, slows down]

16:05.021 --> 16:06.063
[Dante grunts]

16:16.730 --> 16:17.980
Get them out of here. Go!

16:19.271 --> 16:20.188
[man] Dante.

16:20.271 --> 16:22.146
Leaving so soon?

16:22.730 --> 16:25.438
We have much to catch up on, brother.

16:26.230 --> 16:27.230
No.

16:27.938 --> 16:29.313
[mysterious music playing]

16:30.855 --> 16:31.771
You're…

16:31.855 --> 16:33.980
[ethereal metal music playing]

16:34.063 --> 16:35.188
…dead.

16:35.271 --> 16:37.313
Oh, I'm here…

16:38.730 --> 16:39.855
in the flesh!

16:43.105 --> 16:44.105
[grunts]

16:46.521 --> 16:48.521
[frantic electronic music playing]

16:55.855 --> 16:57.980
You're that demon baby from earlier.

17:17.688 --> 17:19.896
[priest] In nomine patris e filii

17:19.980 --> 17:21.896
et spiritus sancti.

17:22.646 --> 17:23.480
Amen.

17:24.063 --> 17:26.355
I don't know anything about any of this.

17:26.438 --> 17:28.688
I just dress up to scam people.

17:32.855 --> 17:34.021
[grunts]

17:34.105 --> 17:35.521
A rabbit demon, eh?

17:35.605 --> 17:37.896
Yeah, maybe I heard something like that.

17:38.563 --> 17:39.521
Talk.

17:40.271 --> 17:42.146
[foreboding music playing]

17:43.063 --> 17:44.396
I know a guy.

17:44.480 --> 17:47.313
He's a broker
for demon hunters and mercenaries.

17:47.396 --> 17:51.438
A hustler who feeds off the bottom
of the bottom feeders.

17:51.521 --> 17:56.646
Last time I saw him, he told me how he'd
set up this job for a talking bunny.

17:56.730 --> 18:00.980
I didn't give him much thought,
coming from a serial liar and a drunk.

18:01.063 --> 18:03.188
But maybe he wasn't lying.

18:03.271 --> 18:05.271
[Dr. Fisher] If we can corroborate this…

18:05.355 --> 18:09.521
[vice president] It means the White Rabbit
was operating here, in New York.

18:09.605 --> 18:11.063
Give me a name.

18:12.396 --> 18:14.063
-[officer 1] Enzo Ferino!
-[officer 2] Go!

18:14.855 --> 18:15.855
Huh?

18:15.938 --> 18:17.313
[club music pulsing]

18:21.563 --> 18:24.188
Coming through! Coming through!
Move it! Move it!

18:24.271 --> 18:26.521
Nice dress. Uh, ooh! Sorry, sweetheart.

18:28.980 --> 18:30.563
[Ferino panting]

18:31.146 --> 18:32.063
[cackling]

18:32.146 --> 18:33.230
-[clang]
-Ow!

18:36.146 --> 18:37.146
[handcuffs clinking]

18:43.605 --> 18:44.646
[Ferino sputtering]

18:44.730 --> 18:46.396
Before we start, you should know

18:46.480 --> 18:49.271
I'll tell you anything you ask me
about any subject.

18:51.313 --> 18:53.855
Now, let's talk compensation.

18:53.938 --> 18:55.438
-[electricity crackles]
-Okay.

18:56.105 --> 18:57.855
Ugh. I'll do it for free.

18:57.938 --> 19:00.480
You guys should learn
how to negotiate properly.

19:00.563 --> 19:02.396
[vice president]
Tell us about the White Rabbit.

19:02.480 --> 19:04.938
[chuckles] That's what this is about?

19:05.021 --> 19:06.938
Yeah, I know who you mean.

19:07.021 --> 19:10.146
He showed up at my office
with a job that needed expediting.

19:10.230 --> 19:12.313
And that didn't seem strange to you?

19:12.396 --> 19:14.480
A six-foot talking rabbit.

19:14.563 --> 19:18.105
Ha! In my line of work,
that's a slow Tuesday.

19:18.730 --> 19:22.563
Some demons making noise over
on the west side that he wanted clipped.

19:22.646 --> 19:25.146
Calling too much attention to themselves
and whatnot.

19:25.230 --> 19:27.563
[vice president]
Why? What did it matter to him?

19:27.646 --> 19:30.980
[Ferino] I saw the price he was offering
and I must have forgot to ask.

19:31.063 --> 19:33.396
One thing about it
that struck me as funny,

19:33.480 --> 19:36.771
he had a particular demon hunter
he wanted me to hire.

19:36.855 --> 19:39.355
-Wouldn't take anyone else.
-[vice president] Who?

19:39.938 --> 19:42.063
Kid named Dante.

19:43.188 --> 19:44.688
Ah, sweet kid.

19:45.188 --> 19:46.855
Bit of a troubled past, though.

19:46.938 --> 19:48.771
You know how it is.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.480
Dad not around.

19:50.563 --> 19:53.563
Mom and twin brother
brutally murdered by demons.

19:53.646 --> 19:55.105
You know, that sort of thing.

19:55.188 --> 19:59.355
Listen. The White Rabbit
told us to find the hunter.

19:59.438 --> 20:03.563
Stands to reason it's the same hunter
that the rabbit personally requested.

20:03.646 --> 20:06.146
Dante. Last name unknown.

20:06.230 --> 20:09.188
Looks like he also works
as a standard hired gun.

20:09.271 --> 20:12.396
Oh! And if half of what
I'm reading here is true,

20:12.480 --> 20:15.146
his capabilities are extraordinary.

20:15.230 --> 20:16.646
What else do we have on him?

20:17.146 --> 20:19.521
Anything that explains
the rabbit's interest?

20:19.605 --> 20:24.188
Hmm. He's recorded as going AWOL
from five separate jobs.

20:24.271 --> 20:25.105
Why?

20:25.188 --> 20:26.938
It just says, uh…

20:27.021 --> 20:28.938
"Got bored"?

20:29.021 --> 20:30.271
[rowdy rock music playing]

20:32.396 --> 20:34.105
Hand over the amulet!

20:45.896 --> 20:46.938
Whoo-hoo!

20:48.021 --> 20:51.313
Dressing up as my dead brother,
a little bit much.

20:51.396 --> 20:53.980
Personally, I would have
stuck with a creepy baby.

20:54.063 --> 20:55.438
It was working for you!

21:13.146 --> 21:14.146
[demon trills] Huh?

21:14.646 --> 21:15.646
[Dante straining]

21:32.230 --> 21:35.771
You've been trying really hard
to steal my necklace.

21:36.438 --> 21:37.271
Why is that?

21:37.355 --> 21:41.688
The irony that I'm the shapeshifter,

21:41.771 --> 21:45.730
and you're the one
who doesn't know what you are.

21:45.813 --> 21:46.730
[energy crackling]

21:47.896 --> 21:49.355
[demon pulsating wetly]

21:53.646 --> 21:54.563
[demon trills]

21:58.980 --> 22:00.563
[sighs] Every time.

22:03.146 --> 22:07.896
I heard a rumor once about demons
who were too powerful to cross over,

22:07.980 --> 22:11.355
so they learned
how to project their consciousness

22:11.438 --> 22:15.188
into our world and possess stuff,
poltergeist-style.

22:15.271 --> 22:18.313
You ask me,
that's what this White Rabbit is.

22:18.396 --> 22:20.521
A possessed kid's toy.

22:20.605 --> 22:21.896
Now, from what I sensed,

22:21.980 --> 22:24.646
he's way more
than just a regular Hell dweller.

22:24.730 --> 22:25.980
I didn't ask.

22:26.063 --> 22:27.855
Look, look, that's all I know.

22:27.938 --> 22:30.063
If you're after his location,
I can't help you.

22:30.146 --> 22:33.063
-I only saw him the one time.
-[vice president] We know his location.

22:33.146 --> 22:37.063
A man-sized rabbit
can only avoid notice for so long.

22:37.146 --> 22:38.730
Even in this labyrinth of sin.

22:39.396 --> 22:41.021
[Ferino] You don't say.

22:41.105 --> 22:43.855
So, you sent a team
in after him then, huh?

22:44.605 --> 22:46.063
Let me guess.

22:46.146 --> 22:47.855
There were no survivors.

22:49.313 --> 22:50.521
Only one.

22:50.605 --> 22:51.438
[gasps]

22:52.646 --> 22:54.188
[panting]

22:54.271 --> 22:55.521
I have an idea.

22:55.605 --> 22:57.396
Ask him about the sword, sir.

22:57.480 --> 23:00.396
[vice president] The Sword of Sparda.
What do you know about it?

23:00.480 --> 23:03.813
Sparda! Ha, boy, that takes me back.

23:03.896 --> 23:05.980
All I know is the old story.

23:06.063 --> 23:07.771
Sparda was an ancient demon,

23:07.855 --> 23:11.813
back in the days when the two realms
were still joined, who sided--

23:11.896 --> 23:14.521
Who sided with humans
to fight his own kind,

23:14.605 --> 23:15.855
the champion of Hell,

23:15.938 --> 23:17.605
until he turned against its king.

23:17.688 --> 23:19.146
I know this story.

23:19.230 --> 23:21.980
What does the sword
have to do with it, though?

23:22.063 --> 23:23.396
I'm getting to it!

23:23.480 --> 23:25.605
So, being such a swell guy,

23:25.688 --> 23:30.105
Sparda takes it on himself
to protect humanity by casting a spell,

23:30.188 --> 23:33.938
creating a wall between the realms,
so to speak.

23:34.021 --> 23:37.480
It was the power of his sword,
apparently, that let him do it,

23:37.563 --> 23:39.396
with the help of a magic amulet,

23:39.480 --> 23:43.521
which he splits in two pieces
to make it harder to find.

23:44.813 --> 23:47.980
Ugh, smells like
some millennial bullshit to me.

23:48.063 --> 23:51.688
That's it. Of course.
Look… Look at this sword here.

23:51.771 --> 23:55.188
See that slot in the hilt?
Though it was meant to hold something?

23:55.271 --> 23:58.730
I theorized that the quantum interference
blocking the rift between realms

23:58.813 --> 24:01.480
was broadcast by some form of transmitter.

24:01.980 --> 24:04.480
Demon technology may look medieval,

24:04.563 --> 24:06.646
but their understanding
of quantum principles

24:06.730 --> 24:08.730
is far more advanced than our own.

24:09.938 --> 24:12.813
This amulet is the transmitter.

24:12.896 --> 24:16.021
Each half of it generates
one half of the signal,

24:16.105 --> 24:18.313
and Sparda's sword is the decoder.

24:18.396 --> 24:21.105
If one were to bring both halves
of the amulet together

24:21.188 --> 24:24.313
and place it into the sword,
the transmission would cease.

24:24.396 --> 24:26.021
There'd be no more interference.

24:26.105 --> 24:29.771
No more wall. The realms would be
open to each other without limit.

24:29.855 --> 24:31.688
You're talking about Armageddon?

24:32.188 --> 24:34.646
Yes. You must understand
what would happen.

24:35.980 --> 24:38.813
The demon who makes
other demons wake up in a cold sweat

24:38.896 --> 24:40.605
will be on our doorstep.

24:41.396 --> 24:43.688
We'll throw everything we have at it,

24:43.771 --> 24:46.813
only to discover that it's not just him.

24:46.896 --> 24:49.355
It's a world full of them.

24:49.438 --> 24:52.230
Our civilization will be overrun.

24:52.730 --> 24:54.188
We won't let it be.

24:54.271 --> 24:56.813
This is DARKCOM's purpose.

24:56.896 --> 24:59.230
This is our divine charge.

24:59.313 --> 25:02.646
To be the last line of defense
against the Inferno.

25:02.730 --> 25:05.730
Right. Our divine charge.

25:05.813 --> 25:09.063
If the rabbit was after the sword,
he must be trying to open the rift,

25:09.146 --> 25:12.063
which means he'll also need
the two amulet pieces.

25:13.146 --> 25:14.855
He already has one.

25:15.938 --> 25:19.313
And not to be an alarmist,
but he's about to get the other one.

25:19.396 --> 25:21.188
Mr. Sir Vice President. Baines.

25:21.271 --> 25:23.438
-[Fisher] Anders, from J-Squad.
-Mr. Vice President, sir.

25:23.521 --> 25:26.438
-The one who survived.
-Good to see you up, soldier.

25:27.480 --> 25:29.896
What did that to your face?

25:29.980 --> 25:31.355
Rabbit claws, sir.

25:31.438 --> 25:34.146
Who let you down here?
Why aren't you in the infirmary?

25:34.230 --> 25:37.105
I have extremely sensitive information
pertaining to… Uh…

25:37.188 --> 25:38.021
Concerning…

25:38.105 --> 25:39.980
Regards to the end of the world, sir.

25:40.063 --> 25:42.938
I had to deliver it, sir.
As in, in person.

25:43.021 --> 25:44.313
To your person.

25:44.896 --> 25:45.730
Sir.

25:45.813 --> 25:48.355
I heard the rabbit say something
after he'd done this.

25:48.438 --> 25:49.688
He was pissed off.

25:49.771 --> 25:51.230
He was furious, sir.

25:51.313 --> 25:53.313
He knows where the other half
of the amulet is.

25:53.396 --> 25:56.271
And he tried to get it back already.
But his plan failed.

25:56.355 --> 25:57.938
He's gonna try again. Soon.

25:58.021 --> 25:59.230
His plan?

25:59.313 --> 26:00.771
What was the plan?

26:01.271 --> 26:04.480
I don't know. Something about hiring
someone for a setup job.

26:04.563 --> 26:05.396
Or something.

26:05.480 --> 26:08.146
Whoever it was,
that's who has the other piece. Sir.

26:08.230 --> 26:10.188
[frenetic, intriguing music playing]

26:13.271 --> 26:14.146
Dante.

26:16.146 --> 26:17.021
Heh.

26:17.105 --> 26:18.980
[chipper dance-pop music playing]

26:24.563 --> 26:25.813
[singer] ♪ Okay ♪

26:38.271 --> 26:39.521
[singer] ♪ Okay ♪

26:41.313 --> 26:43.021
[music swells, trails off]

26:43.105 --> 26:44.521
[console beeps, thuds]

26:44.605 --> 26:45.813
[applause]

26:45.896 --> 26:47.271
[game announcer] Game over!

26:47.355 --> 26:48.355
[Dante] Aw!

26:51.521 --> 26:52.521
[energy thrumming]

26:58.438 --> 26:59.438
["Devils Never Cry" plays]

26:59.521 --> 27:00.896
♪ Bless me ♪

27:00.980 --> 27:06.980
♪ With the leaf off of the tree ♪

27:07.063 --> 27:10.896
♪ On it, I see ♪

27:10.980 --> 27:14.855
♪ The freedom reign ♪

27:14.938 --> 27:18.730
♪ We are falling ♪

27:18.813 --> 27:22.563
♪ The light is calling ♪

27:22.646 --> 27:26.480
♪ Tears inside me ♪

27:26.563 --> 27:30.438
♪ Calm me down ♪

27:30.521 --> 27:34.230
♪ Midnight calling ♪

27:34.313 --> 27:38.146
♪ Mist of resolving ♪

27:38.230 --> 27:40.188
♪ Crown me ♪

27:40.271 --> 27:46.021
♪ With the pure, green leaf ♪

27:46.105 --> 27:49.896
♪ Praise to my father ♪

27:49.980 --> 27:53.813
♪ Blessed by the water ♪

27:53.896 --> 27:57.855
♪ Black light, dark sky ♪

27:57.938 --> 27:59.646
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY (1955-2022)

27:59.730 --> 28:02.646
♪ The devil's cry ♪